After working on project and making it
* add shebang syntax to set enviornment
1 do npm init -y (in terminal) to make package json files (done in order to link with npm and make it global)
2 in package json file write a thing "bin":{
    the name that you want to give it as when you want to install the npm package(this tool) you can use this name as npm name
}

example "bin":{
    "edin":"main.js"
}

edin name points to main.js file

3 in terminal write npm link to link with npm